Node - Env to run JS outside of the browser
NPM - Node Package Manager - GitHub
Yarn - FaceBook

Check Node Version :
> node -v

Check NPM Version :
> npm -v

Initialize :
> npm init
> npm init -y

Default Init Config Values :
> npm config set init-author-name Guvi
> npm config set init-license MIT
> npm config set init-author-name Guvi init-license MIT

> npm config get init-author-name
Guvi
> npm config get init-license
MIT
> npm config get

> npm config delete init-author-name
> npm config delete init-license
> npm config delete init-author-name init-license

Manage Packages :
> npm install lodash
> npm install lodash react
> npm i lodash
> npm i lodash@4.16.0
> npm i eslint --save-dev
> npm i eslint -g
> npm root -g
> npm install
> npm install --only=prod
> npm uninstall react
> npm remove react
> npm list --depth=1

lodash: "^4.16.0"
=> Latest version for my major version
=> 4.17.21

lodash: ~4.16.0
=> Latest patch version for my major and minor version
=> 4.16.6

Scripts :
> npm start (Inbuilt commands)
> npm run guvi (Custom Commands
